After that, it iterates through each character in the second string and checks if the character exists in the frequency counter object. If it doesn't, it means the characters are different, so it returns `false`. Otherwise, it decrements the frequency counter for that character.

Finally, it checks if all frequencies in the counter object are zero. If any frequency is non-zero, it means there are extra characters in one of the strings, so it returns `false`. If all frequencies are zero, it means the strings are anagrams, so it returns `true`.

